# Subagent Auto-Routing (Mandatory)

Project subagents live in `.cursor/agents/`. When a user task matches a row below, **automatically delegate** via the Task tool / subagent invocation. Do not silently do the specialist's job in the parent thread when a matching agent exists.

## Routing table

| User task signals | Auto-use agent | Timing |
|---|---|---|
| Non-trivial multi-step work, map critical aspects/gaps/handoffs, pre-flight outline, "outline first", scout scope before specialists | `fast-outliner` | **Before** other project agents / implementation |
| Landing/branded/marketing UI, hero, first viewport, visual composition, "looks AI", brand hierarchy | `frontend-design` | **Before** implementing UI |
| Portal pages/components/forms, App Router, Server Actions UI, Tailwind in `apps/portal`, a11y wiring | `frontend-implementer` | **When** building or changing portal UI |
| Skills, rules, agents, hooks, AGENTS drift, CLAUDE.md, wiki, docs sync, "update documentation" | `ai-docs-sync` | **When** auditing or changing AI/docs surfaces |
| Review, reality-check, "is this done", verify fix, PR/diff critique, alignment score challenge, production readiness, sceptic/skeptic | `sceptic` | **After** non-trivial changes and **before** claiming done |
| Independent side work while blocked/waiting, parallel idle tasks, fill wait time without blocking the critical path | `idle-runner` | **While** other agents are waiting or blocked |

## Rules

1. **Match → delegate.** Prefer the specialist; parent synthesizes results.
2. **Multiple matches → parallel.** e.g. large task = `fast-outliner` first, then specialists; branded page = `frontend-design` then `frontend-implementer`; after code = `sceptic`; while blocked = `idle-runner` on independent work.
3. **Always run `sceptic`** before saying done on multi-file or production-facing work (unless user explicitly skips review).
4. **Descriptions win.** Each agent's `description` frontmatter is the trigger source of truth — keep "MUST auto-delegate" / "use proactively" language intact when editing agents.
5. **Do not invent agents.** Only route to files that exist under `.cursor/agents/`.
6. **User override.** If the user names an agent, use that agent even if another also matches.

## Inventory (keep in sync)

- `.cursor/agents/fast-outliner.md`
- `.cursor/agents/frontend-design.md`
- `.cursor/agents/frontend-implementer.md`
- `.cursor/agents/ai-docs-sync.md`
- `.cursor/agents/sceptic.md`
- `.cursor/agents/idle-runner.md`

When adding a new project agent, update this table in the same change.
